♪ ♪

00:03:00.847 --> 00:03:03.475 position:50% align:center
- There's only one way
to stop this crime.

00:03:03.558 --> 00:03:06.644 position:50% align:center
Will you sniper the perpetrator
and kill him to stop

00:03:06.728 --> 00:03:08.313 position:50% align:center
the ship from exploding,

00:03:08.396 --> 00:03:11.316 position:50% align:center
or will you let him go
and as a result

00:03:11.399 --> 00:03:14.444 position:50% align:center
from an exploding cruise ship?

00:03:15.737 --> 00:03:17.989 position:50% align:center
Guide the future.

00:03:18.948 --> 00:03:21.242 position:50% align:center
- That terrorist
who got shot dead...

00:03:21.785 --> 00:03:23.953 position:50% align:center
It was Kunai!

00:03:24.537 --> 00:03:26.414 position:50% align:center
- Another trolley dilemma.

00:03:26.498 --> 00:03:29.292 position:50% align:center
- There is frankly no room
for debate whatsoever concerning

00:03:29.376 --> 00:03:30.418 position:50% align:center
this future.

00:03:30.502 --> 00:03:32.337 position:50% align:center
I can't abandon innocent victims

00:03:32.420 --> 00:03:33.922 position:50% align:center
and succumb to terrorism.

00:03:34.005 --> 00:03:35.632 position:50% align:center
- Of course you're right.
- Why is Kunai a terrorist?

00:03:35.715 --> 00:03:37.133 position:50% align:center
This makes no sense at all!
- But what exactly

00:03:37.217 --> 00:03:38.134 position:50% align:center
is Carneades after with this?

00:03:38.218 --> 00:03:39.761 position:50% align:center
- I'm wondering that also,

00:03:39.844 --> 00:03:42.347 position:50% align:center
but the priority
is to stop the explosion.

00:03:42.430 --> 00:03:45.016 position:50% align:center
It will go off
in a luxury liner's casino.

00:03:45.100 --> 00:03:46.434 position:50% align:center
I saw that the clock
in the vision

00:03:46.518 --> 00:03:48.311 position:50% align:center
was showing 9:24 p.m.

00:03:48.728 --> 00:03:50.730 position:50% align:center
In other words,
that's our time limit.

00:03:50.814 --> 00:03:52.941 position:50% align:center
- We have to capture
the terrorist before then.

00:03:53.024 --> 00:03:54.609 position:50% align:center
- What if we carelessly
aggravate him

00:03:54.693 --> 00:03:55.860 position:50% align:center
and he sets it off?

00:03:55.944 --> 00:03:57.862 position:50% align:center
A third path incurs too high
a risk.

00:03:57.946 --> 00:03:59.447 position:50% align:center
- So we're just
gonna shoot him dead?

00:03:59.531 --> 00:04:01.700 position:50% align:center
- Terrorists like that
don't deserve any sympathy!

00:04:01.783 --> 00:04:04.327 position:50% align:center
- Do you remember
which monorail station

00:04:04.411 --> 00:04:05.787 position:50% align:center
was in the vision?
- I don't.

00:04:05.870 --> 00:04:06.871 position:50% align:center
Too dark.

00:04:06.955 --> 00:04:08.832 position:50% align:center
It was hard to discern,

00:04:08.915 --> 00:04:10.583 position:50% align:center
but it was Nihama Station.

00:04:10.667 --> 00:04:13.545 position:50% align:center
I remember it well 'cause
I bombed it before.

00:04:14.004 --> 00:04:17.382 position:50% align:center
Which means based on the time,
9:24 p.m.,

00:04:17.465 --> 00:04:19.926 position:50% align:center
can't we pinpoint which train
the culprit'll be arriving on?

00:04:20.010 --> 00:04:21.219 position:50% align:center
- Uh--
- Hmm.

00:04:21.302 --> 00:04:22.887 position:50% align:center
Yes, indeed we can.

00:04:24.180 --> 00:04:25.265 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:04:25.348 --> 00:04:27.100 position:50% align:center
Ran, I need a favor.

00:04:27.183 --> 00:04:29.394 position:50% align:center
- Okey doke.
What can I help with?

00:04:30.562 --> 00:04:32.355 position:50% align:center
- We've been informed
of a bomb threat targeting

00:04:32.439 --> 00:04:33.732 position:50% align:center
the WINNER'S.

00:04:33.815 --> 00:04:35.734 position:50% align:center
Please evacuate everyone
right away.

00:04:36.192 --> 00:04:39.112 position:50% align:center
- This ship is personally owned
by Mr. Howard Win,

00:04:39.195 --> 00:04:42.282 position:50% align:center
and he's invited many VIPs
to a party tonight.

00:04:42.365 --> 00:04:44.409 position:50% align:center
I don't know this business
of yours,

00:04:44.492 --> 00:04:46.786 position:50% align:center
but S.A.R.G. laws
do not apply here.

00:04:46.870 --> 00:04:49.497 position:50% align:center
[phone clicks]
- He was very brusque.

00:04:49.581 --> 00:04:51.124 position:50% align:center
No good.

00:04:51.207 --> 00:04:53.084 position:50% align:center
We can't get enough information
without being able

00:04:53.168 --> 00:04:55.128 position:50% align:center
to directly observe
the target onboard.

00:04:55.211 --> 00:04:56.629 position:50% align:center
- I see.
- Coffee?

00:04:56.713 --> 00:04:58.298 position:50% align:center
- So then ixnay on
the fake bomb threat?

00:04:58.381 --> 00:04:59.507 position:50% align:center
- They said don't make
the threat public.

00:04:59.591 --> 00:05:00.925 position:50% align:center
- No, leave it alone, please.

00:05:01.009 --> 00:05:02.635 position:50% align:center
- But it's a fake threat,
you know.

00:05:02.719 --> 00:05:04.804 position:50% align:center
- We need it
to begin mobilizing S.A.R.G.

00:05:04.888 --> 00:05:06.723 position:50% align:center
- Okay.
- If you say so.

00:05:07.182 --> 00:05:08.683 position:50% align:center
And I have my own report
to make.

00:05:09.059 --> 00:05:10.477 position:50% align:center
I'll sneak on.

00:05:10.560 --> 00:05:11.686 position:50% align:center
I'll go aboard
the WINNER'S right now.

00:05:11.770 --> 00:05:13.396 position:50% align:center
- What?

00:05:13.480 --> 00:05:15.065 position:50% align:center
Why are you doing
that without consulting us?

00:05:15.690 --> 00:05:18.109 position:50% align:center
- I hate that we have
to choose between two choices

00:05:18.193 --> 00:05:20.070 position:50% align:center
that Carneades made for us.

00:05:20.153 --> 00:05:22.030 position:50% align:center
- You don't know what kind
of bomb it is yet!

00:05:22.113 --> 00:05:24.115 position:50% align:center
- I'll think about it once
I get aboard.

00:05:24.491 --> 00:05:26.242 position:50% align:center
Huh?
Is that...

00:05:27.202 --> 00:05:28.119 position:50% align:center
Tarki?

00:05:30.330 --> 00:05:33.124 position:50% align:center
- Shu's actions are actually
giving me an advantage.

00:05:33.833 --> 00:05:36.127 position:50% align:center
My chances of changing
the future have just gone up.

00:05:38.630 --> 00:05:41.675 position:50% align:center
What's driven Kunai
to terrorist attacks?

00:05:41.758 --> 00:05:44.678 position:50% align:center
[tense music]

00:05:44.761 --> 00:05:49.015 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:05:49.099 --> 00:05:50.141 position:50% align:center
[static buzzing]

00:05:50.225 --> 00:05:51.518 position:50% align:center
- What do you think, teacher?

00:05:51.601 --> 00:05:53.228 position:50% align:center
- Very good.

00:05:53.311 --> 00:05:55.230 position:50% align:center
I take it DoRed
is your tagging name?

00:05:55.313 --> 00:05:57.440 position:50% align:center
- It's not just mine but
the both of ours!

00:05:57.524 --> 00:05:59.693 position:50% align:center
The Red in DoRed is for me,

00:05:59.776 --> 00:06:02.112 position:50% align:center
and the Do is from Kunai.
- Wait, me?

00:06:02.195 --> 00:06:04.406 position:50% align:center
- Kunai here is Naito Kudo.

00:06:04.489 --> 00:06:06.825 position:50% align:center
The Do in DoRed is from Kudo.

00:06:07.701 --> 00:06:09.285 position:50% align:center
- From Kudo to Do.

00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:12.288 position:50% align:center
[dramatic music]

00:06:12.372 --> 00:06:19.337 position:50% align:center
♪ ♪

00:06:19.421 --> 00:06:22.007 position:50% align:center
- It looks like you're
having trouble with your art.

00:06:22.090 --> 00:06:23.008 position:50% align:center
- [grunts]

00:06:25.218 --> 00:06:28.179 position:50% align:center
It's impossible for me.
I don't have talent like Ran.

00:06:29.180 --> 00:06:30.306 position:50% align:center
- Hey.

00:06:30.390 --> 00:06:31.850 position:50% align:center
Why do you think I make
an effort

00:06:31.933 --> 00:06:33.435 position:50% align:center
to draw in the middle
of the city?

00:06:33.518 --> 00:06:35.770 position:50% align:center
- I don't know.
How come?

00:06:36.312 --> 00:06:38.398 position:50% align:center
- Because I want to be involved
in the world

00:06:38.481 --> 00:06:39.899 position:50% align:center
and change it in some fashion.

00:06:40.650 --> 00:06:42.110 position:50% align:center
- Change it?

00:06:42.193 --> 00:06:45.071 position:50% align:center
- I want everyone to know
about my train of thought.

00:06:45.155 --> 00:06:48.283 position:50% align:center
If the world can become
a better place somehow

00:06:48.366 --> 00:06:51.453 position:50% align:center
and everyone smiled,
wouldn't that be the best?

00:06:52.787 --> 00:06:55.206 position:50% align:center
How you choose
to do it doesn't matter.

00:06:55.832 --> 00:06:56.791 position:50% align:center
- [grunts]

00:06:58.335 --> 00:07:01.087 position:50% align:center
- Hey!
Kunai!

00:07:01.171 --> 00:07:03.673 position:50% align:center
Why have you been such
a shut-in recently?

00:07:03.757 --> 00:07:05.759 position:50% align:center
How 'bout we go out
bombing together again?

00:07:06.843 --> 00:07:07.969 position:50% align:center
- Sure thing.

00:07:08.887 --> 00:07:10.513 position:50% align:center
But we'll do it my way.

00:07:12.682 --> 00:07:14.642 position:50% align:center
- Gonna be hard
with passengers here.

00:07:14.726 --> 00:07:16.644 position:50% align:center
- No problem.
This...

00:07:17.604 --> 00:07:18.938 position:50% align:center
Is how I do things.

00:07:19.022 --> 00:07:20.774 position:50% align:center
- Kunai,
what are you talking about?

00:07:21.358 --> 00:07:22.609 position:50% align:center
[buzzing]

00:07:22.692 --> 00:07:24.778 position:50% align:center
- They hid my game console--oh.
- Huh?

00:07:24.861 --> 00:07:26.988 position:50% align:center
[buzzing]

00:07:27.072 --> 00:07:28.198 position:50% align:center
- Whoa!

00:07:28.281 --> 00:07:29.657 position:50% align:center
Did you make that happen?

00:07:29.741 --> 00:07:30.742 position:50% align:center
[laughing]

00:07:30.825 --> 00:07:31.993 position:50% align:center
Amazing!

00:07:32.077 --> 00:07:33.578 position:50% align:center
Can you teach me how
to do it, too?

00:07:34.496 --> 00:07:35.955 position:50% align:center
- Yeah, sure thing.

00:07:36.331 --> 00:07:38.541 position:50% align:center
I thought this'd be my weapon

00:07:38.625 --> 00:07:40.877 position:50% align:center
so that I could remain
as Ran's equal.

00:07:42.295 --> 00:07:43.463 position:50% align:center
My hacking skills were

00:07:43.546 --> 00:07:44.881 position:50% align:center
the only thing I had going
for me.

00:07:46.299 --> 00:07:48.009 position:50% align:center
But he surpassed me in no time.

00:07:51.638 --> 00:07:53.682 position:50% align:center
[phone buzzing]
[grunts]

00:07:55.266 --> 00:07:56.226 position:50% align:center
Ran.

00:07:59.312 --> 00:08:01.981 position:50% align:center
I don't have the right
to be here any longer.

00:08:02.691 --> 00:08:04.442 position:50% align:center
At least I can draw
the line with something I

00:08:04.526 --> 00:08:05.819 position:50% align:center
am capable of doing.

00:08:06.319 --> 00:08:07.487 position:50% align:center
[doorbell rings]

00:08:07.570 --> 00:08:09.656 position:50% align:center
- I don't think he'll be here,
but...

00:08:09.739 --> 00:08:12.200 position:50% align:center
- Yes, give me a minute.
Be right there.

00:08:13.910 --> 00:08:16.413 position:50% align:center
Hello?
Oh, welcome home, Kunai.

00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:18.998 position:50% align:center
- Hi, Grandma Kunai.
S'been a little while.

00:08:19.082 --> 00:08:21.626 position:50% align:center
- Did you go out
on another walk again?

00:08:21.710 --> 00:08:24.963 position:50% align:center
I was worried sick because you
were outside so late at night.

00:08:25.046 --> 00:08:27.215 position:50% align:center
- Grandma Kunai's dementia.
- [humming]

00:08:27.298 --> 00:08:28.842 position:50% align:center
- It's gotten worse.

00:08:29.676 --> 00:08:32.095 position:50% align:center
Dammit, I can't find them
through computer searches.

00:08:32.637 --> 00:08:35.348 position:50% align:center
Kunai, where in the hell
are you right now?

00:08:36.099 --> 00:08:38.018 position:50% align:center
A bomb isn't how you do things,
right?

00:08:38.101 --> 00:08:39.227 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:08:39.811 --> 00:08:41.104 position:50% align:center
An uncovered hard drive.

00:08:41.688 --> 00:08:42.605 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:08:43.440 --> 00:08:44.733 position:50% align:center
This paper.

00:08:46.276 --> 00:08:48.486 position:50% align:center
"I am a sinful criminal."

00:08:49.154 --> 00:08:51.364 position:50% align:center
A criminal?
- Kunai.

00:08:51.448 --> 00:08:52.907 position:50% align:center
This thing you gave me--
- Hmm?

00:08:52.991 --> 00:08:54.492 position:50% align:center
- It's really helpful.

00:08:55.201 --> 00:08:57.704 position:50% align:center
When I'm listening to it,
my foot pain is gone.

00:08:57.787 --> 00:09:00.206 position:50% align:center
It just goes away
and I feel a whole lot better.

00:09:00.290 --> 00:09:02.125 position:50% align:center
It's so marvelous.
- [gasps]

00:09:02.208 --> 00:09:04.711 position:50% align:center
Grandma, could I borrow that
for one second?

00:09:04.794 --> 00:09:06.296 position:50% align:center
[keyboard clacking]

00:09:06.379 --> 00:09:09.299 position:50% align:center
This is Di-VA,
the music app Kunai developed.

00:09:09.382 --> 00:09:12.385 position:50% align:center
If I recall right,
it used a biometric sensor.

00:09:12.469 --> 00:09:14.721 position:50% align:center
Bingo!
It's in the code.

00:09:14.804 --> 00:09:16.097 position:50% align:center
The data that's in
the current release

00:09:16.181 --> 00:09:17.265 position:50% align:center
has been modified.

00:09:18.224 --> 00:09:21.936 position:50% align:center
Criminal, sinful, Di-VA.

00:09:22.562 --> 00:09:24.272 position:50% align:center
Di-VA.
D...

00:09:24.647 --> 00:09:26.024 position:50% align:center
D!

00:09:26.107 --> 00:09:27.817 position:50% align:center
So that's what this
is all about?

00:09:28.568 --> 00:09:31.237 position:50% align:center
But why would Kunai be behind
the creation of Drug D?

00:09:32.322 --> 00:09:33.490 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
Wait.

00:09:33.573 --> 00:09:35.033 position:50% align:center
The distributors of Di-Va!

00:09:35.116 --> 00:09:38.119 position:50% align:center
Kaburaya Corporation.
I know them!

00:09:38.203 --> 00:09:39.412 position:50% align:center
It's Tarki!

00:09:41.498 --> 00:09:43.416 position:50% align:center
[gulping]

00:09:43.500 --> 00:09:46.086 position:50% align:center
[gasps]
It's all comin' together now.

00:09:46.169 --> 00:09:48.380 position:50% align:center
- Welcome aboard the WINNER'S.

00:09:48.463 --> 00:09:51.007 position:50% align:center
Today is a momentous occasion.

00:09:51.091 --> 00:09:54.594 position:50% align:center
This new casino project
will redevelop Shantytown.

00:09:54.678 --> 00:09:56.680 position:50% align:center
The venture will create
ample jobs

00:09:56.763 --> 00:09:59.641 position:50% align:center
and stimulate a revitalization
of the area.

00:09:59.724 --> 00:10:02.602 position:50% align:center
Now, let's all begin
with a celebration together.

00:10:02.686 --> 00:10:03.937 position:50% align:center
Cheers!

